      "channelName": "💬-discussion",
      "summary": "The discussion centered on concerns about ElizaOS project status and a Bitget exchange delisting announcement. Community members questioned why the ElizaOS X account hadn't posted since March, with some expressing bearish sentiment. The main issue was Bitget's announcement to delist ELIZAOS/USDT trading pair on April 17, 2026, along with 6 other pairs. Odilitime clarified that the team never communicated with Bitget about the listing. He addressed misconceptions about the project being a \"low mcap gem\" or \"unknown token,\" stating they aimed for blue chip status. Odilitime acknowledged communication challenges, noting the team continues working as they did last year but struggles to convey their vision to the market. He expressed concern that investors don't understand or believe in what they're building, attributing lack of buy pressure to this disconnect. While taking responsibility for communication failures, he suggested the project might be a \"failed experiment\" if they can't bridge the understanding gap with the market.",
